This paper uses satellite images and deep learning techniques to predict county-level mortality rates in the United States. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it involves the analysis and interpretation of visual data. Additionally, it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as it uses deep learning techniques to make predictions. The paper also involves the analysis of geographical features, such as sidewalks, driveways, and hiking trails, which could place it in the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on public health interventions could also place it in the Social and Information Sciences (cs.SI) sub-category.
